<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authority="Haliday" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aptinothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aptinothrips Haliday</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
The four species included in this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Mirab-balou, M" journalOrPublisher="Natura Montenegrina" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="435 - 466" title="Iranian Thripinae with ctenidia laterally on the abdominal tergites (Thysanoptera: Thripidae)." volume="10" year="2011 a">Mirab-balou et al. 2011a</bibRefCitation>
) are all apterous. Three of these are known from Iran: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aptinothrips elegans" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">Aptinothrips elegans</taxonomicName>
Priesner, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aptinothrips rufus" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">Aptinothrips rufus</taxonomicName>
(Haliday) and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Aptinothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aptinothrips stylifer" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylifer">Aptinothrips stylifer</taxonomicName>
Trybom (
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Bhatti et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is included in the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Anaphothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anaphothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anaphothrips</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 76" title="Australian Thripinae of the Anaphothrips genus-group (Thysanoptera), with three new genera and thirty-three new species." volume="2042" year="2009">Mound and Masumoto 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
